link:reference.tech.01.02:FullReferenceText: The pre rules means the amendments made by Part 1 to Schedule 3 of the Tax Laws Amendment (2012 measures No.2) Act 2012. The proposed rules on the changes to IOP, SIC and administrative penalties were introduced in Schedule 3 to the Tax Laws Amendment (2012 Measures No.4) Bill 2012 on 27 June 2012.

The interim rules means the amendments made by Parts 1 and 2 to Schedule 3 of the Tax Laws Amendment (2012 measures No.2) Act 2012. The proposed rules on the changes to IOP, SIC and administrative penalties were introduced in Schedule 3 to the Tax Laws Amendment (2012 measures No.4) Bill 2012 on 27 June 2012.
The prospective rules means the amendments made by Parts 1, 2 and 3 to Schedule 3 of the Tax Laws Amendment (2012 measures No.2) Act 2012.
